---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="DFOS Protocol"
  description="Ed25519 signed chains, content-addressed proofs, W3C DIDs. Verifiable identity and content without trusting the platform."
  landing={true}
>
  <!-- ═══ Hero ═══ -->
  <section class="hero hero--forest">
    <header class="site-header">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <img src="/dfos-logo-green.svg" alt="DFOS" />
      </a>
      <nav>
        <a href="/overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="/spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="/did-method">DID</a>
        <a href="/content-model">Content</a>
        <a href="/web-relay">Relay</a>
        <a href="/cli">CLI</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <div class="hero-inner">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="hero-key" />
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The proof is public<span class="period">.</span><br />
        The content is private<span class="period">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">
        Ed25519 signed DAGs &middot; content-addressed CIDs &middot; W3C DIDs &middot; MIT License
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Two Surfaces ═══ -->
  <section class="split-section">
    <div class="split-image">
      <img src="/painting-hand.jpg" alt="" />
    </div>
    <div class="split-text">
      <span class="section-label">T O P O L O G Y</span>
      <h2>Two surfaces<span class="period">.</span></h2>
      <p>
        The proof surface is public. Signed chains of cryptographic commitments —
        verifiable by anyone with a public key and any standard Ed25519 library.
        Verification is a pure function: given the chain data and a public key,
        the answer is valid or invalid. No network call required.
      </p>
      <p>
        The content surface is private. Documents live in member-governed spaces,
        visible only to participants. The protocol defines the proof surface and
        sees only hashes, never documents. Proofs, not posts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Chain Topology ═══ -->
  <section class="dark-section">
    <div class="dark-section-inner">
      <span class="section-label">S T R U C T U R E</span>
      <h2>Identity is a signed DAG<span class="period">.</span></h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <p>
            An identity chain is a directed acyclic graph of Ed25519-signed operations
            rooted at a genesis. Each operation — key rotation, content commitment,
            recovery — links to its predecessor via content-addressed CID. Forks are
            valid. Convergence is deterministic: highest timestamp among tips, lexicographic
            CID as tiebreaker. Any implementation with the same operations computes
            the same head.
          </p>
          <p>
            The DID derives from the hash of the genesis operation, making identity
            self-certifying. Given the chain data, anyone can verify it belongs to
            the claimed <a href="/did-method"><code>did:dfos</code></a> identifier.
            The chain carries everything needed to verify itself.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>
            Content chains use the same mechanics — a signed sequence of commitments
            to content-addressed documents. The protocol doesn't know what a "post"
            is. Application semantics live in a
            <a href="/content-model">separate content layer</a>, free to evolve
            without protocol changes.
          </p>
          <p>
            Verification works across five languages — TypeScript, Go, Python, Rust,
            Swift — all running against the same
            <a href="/spec#deterministic-reference-artifacts">deterministic test vectors</a>.
            A chain exported today is verifiable by code that doesn't exist yet.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="chain-diagram">
        <div class="chain-node genesis">genesis</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node">rotate</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node">commit</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node">commit</div>
        <div class="chain-edge"></div>
        <div class="chain-node head">head</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Image Break ═══ -->
  <section class="image-break">
    <img src="/painting-deer.jpg" alt="" class="image-break-bg" />
    <div class="image-break-overlay">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="image-break-key" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Specifications ═══ -->
  <section class="landing-section">
    <span class="section-label">S P E C I F I C A T I O N S</span>
    <h2>Read the protocol<span class="period">.</span></h2>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <a href="/spec" class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Protocol Specification</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          Identity chains, content chains, beacons, merkle trees,
          countersignatures, CID derivation, verification rules, test vectors.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/did-method" class="card">
        <div class="card-title">DID Method</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          W3C DID method for <code>did:dfos</code> — self-certifying,
          transport-agnostic decentralized identifiers.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/content-model" class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Content Model</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          JSON Schema content types — post, profile, manifest —
          committed via content-addressed CIDs.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/web-relay" class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Web Relay</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          Verifying HTTP relay with gossip, read-through, and sync peering.
          Emergent network topology from per-peer configuration.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/cli" class="card">
        <div class="card-title">CLI</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          Go command-line tool for managing identities, signing operations,
          and interacting with relays.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/overview" class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Overview</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          Why the protocol exists, chain topology, the relay network,
          verification model, design principles.
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="section-divider" />

  <!-- ═══ Resources ═══ -->
  <section class="landing-section">
    <span class="section-label">R E S O U R C E S</span>
    <h2>Go deeper<span class="period">.</span></h2>

    <ul class="resource-list">
      <li>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <span class="desc">— design decisions, comparison to AT Protocol, blockchain identity</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/poster">Architecture Poster</a>
        <span class="desc">— visual protocol reference</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://schemas.dfos.com">schemas.dfos.com</a>
        <span class="desc">— hosted JSON Schema definitions</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-protocol">npm</a>
        <span class="desc">— @metalabel/dfos-protocol, <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@metalabel/dfos-web-relay">@metalabel/dfos-web-relay</a></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
        <span class="desc">— metalabel/dfos — MIT License</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://verify.dfos.com">Chain Verifier</a>
        <span class="desc">— verify chains in the browser</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/llms-full.txt">llms-full.txt</a>
        <span class="desc">— complete protocol content as plain text</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Closing ═══ -->
  <footer class="closing">
    <div class="closing-image">
      <img src="/painting-angel.jpg" alt="" />
    </div>
    <div class="closing-content">
      <img src="/key-icon-green.svg" alt="" class="closing-key" />
      <div class="closing-mark">DFOS Protocol</div>
      <nav class="closing-nav">
        <a href="/overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="/spec">Spec</a>
        <a href="/did-method">DID</a>
        <a href="/content-model">Content</a>
        <a href="/web-relay">Relay</a>
        <a href="/cli">CLI</a>
        <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://dfos.com">dfos.com</a>
      </nav>
      <p class="closing-credits">Yancey &middot; Ilya &middot; Brandon &middot; Lena</p>
      <p class="closing-credits"><a href="https://github.com/metalabel/dfos/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT License</a> &middot; 2026</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
